  "text": "To have a fair comparison in terms of the effects of the PWM supply on the iron losses [CITATION_1] , the same modulation index was used in the corresponding three-phase and DTP tests. Hence, the inverter dc link voltage during the three-phase tests must be almost double compared to that used for the DTP operation; this ensures that duty-cycles of inverter commands in the corresponding cases are almost identical, as shown in Figs. 9 and 10. As a consequence, the influence of the PWM operation on the machine iron losses is the same for the two cases.",
